trans-unit.source: You are about to annotate outlet types that have been predicated by a computer. To measure, analyse and understand if these outlet types are correct we need your help. You will see a Outlet names and the prediction of the Outlet type (in Blue). In most cases you will also see on what information this predication is based on. A prediction can be annotated as correct, incorrect or you do not know.
If you believe the prediction is correct, press the green button Correct or use the right arrow button on your keyboard.

If you think it the prediction is incorrect, press the red button Incorrect or use the left arrow button on your keyboard. When Incorrect you are being asked to point out the correct Outlet type, either by selecting from the list or select box.

If you are unsure or simply don’t know, please use the Unknown button or question mark button (without shift). It can happen that you have made a mistake and you want to change your judgement. On the left hand side you will find a history of your annotations, select the one you want to change. Let’s get started, if you have further questions please do not hesitate to contact your Data manager.
